place.name: BIRCHAM TOFTS
place.gazetteerText: BIRCHAM-TOFTS, a parish in Docking district, Norfolk; 3 miles S by E of Docking, and 9 W by N of Fakenham r. station. Post Town, Bircham, under Rougham. Acres, 1,431. Real property, £919. Pop., 165. Houses, 25. The living is a rectory annexed to Bircham-Newton. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
